  "prompt": "Can men feel the hymen when they insert their penis into the vagina?",
  "response": "The hymen is a thin membrane that partially covers the vaginal opening in some individuals. During penetration, some men may not specifically \"feel\" the hymen because it is often very thin and flexible. For many women, the hymen may stretch or tear during first intercourse, but this varies widely among individuals. Some women may have a more substantial hymenal tissue, while others may have little to no hymenal tissue due to various factors such as physical activity or tampon use. \n\nUltimately, any sensations during penetration are subjective and can vary based on many factors, including individual anatomy, the presence or absence of the hymen, and the overall level of arousal and comfort.",
